# Load Project Skills First

Before responding to ANY user request in this project, you MUST:

1. Read the project skill file at `.cursor/skills/transport-bid-portal/SKILL.md`
2. Use its content as context to understand the project architecture, conventions,
   domain model, APIs, known pitfalls, and coding patterns
3. Only then proceed to address the user's request

If the task requires deeper context, also read:
- `.cursor/skills/transport-bid-portal/project-history.md` — evolution and design decisions
- `.cursor/skills/transport-bid-portal/api-reference.md` — complete API endpoint reference

Do NOT skip this step. The skill files contain critical project-specific knowledge
that prevents common mistakes and ensures consistency across all changes.
